{
  "id": "piston-door-2x2",
  "title": "2x2 Piston Door",
  "category": "door",
  "description": "A compact 2x2 sliding door built from four sticky pistons. Two pistons above the opening face down and two below face up; when powered they each shove a stone block into the 2x2 gap (door closed), and when the power is cut their sticky heads pull those blocks back out (door open). A single lever drives all four pistons through a redstone line that climbs the back of the wall, so one flip opens or closes the whole door.",
